net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class FileField

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.FileField
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, Component, ListCellRenderer, TableCellRenderer

    @Configurable
@ConfigurableObject
@UIElement(supportsAction=true,
           name="field")
public class FileField
extends ComponentImpl
implements TableCellRenderer, ListCellRenderer

    The FileField provides a mechanism for specifying a file and methods to retrieve the contents of the file and various metadata.

    This component may be used as a list or table cell renderer. The appropriate cell renderer method must be called to behave correctly as a cell renderer.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com), originally written by Tiong Lee (tlee@i2rd.com)

        public Element getHTMLElement()
        Description copied from interface: Component
        Get the top level elements this component will output in its current state. This should not included the entire content model.

        For example, if your code outputs the following, <p><span><b></b></span></p>, then you should only return one element that is a "p"; NOT "p, span, b".

        All configuration elements should be nested within this top element, or other arrangements should be made with the inner keeper.

      • setAccept

        public void setAccept(@Nullable
             String accept)
        Set the acceptable mime types for file upload. This is a hint to the browser and may not work on all browser and operating system combinations. You can specify a single mime type or multiple.

        Examples:

        • setAccept("audio/*");
        • setAccept("video/*");
        • setAccept("image/*");
        • setAccept("audio/*, video/*");
        • setAccept("image/png, image/gif");
        Parameters:
        accept - a comma delimited set of mimetypes.
